Great! To make the calendar icon open the calendar when clicked, you need to:

1. Attach the mat-datepicker-toggle properly.


2. Make sure the calendar icon acts as the trigger.



✅ Here’s the updated HTML snippet for the date picker section:

Replace your existing date section in exchange-rates.component.html with this:

<label>Effective Date</label>
<div class="datepicker-container">
  <input [matDatepicker]="picker" [(ngModel)]="formModel.effectiveDate" />
  <mat-datepicker-toggle [for]="picker" matSuffix></mat-datepicker-toggle>
  <mat-datepicker #picker></mat-datepicker>
</div>

✅ And add this CSS to position the icon nicely:

In exchange-rates.component.css, add:

.datepicker-container {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
}


---

✅ Ensure You’ve Imported These:

In your app.config.ts (or module):

import { MatDatepickerModule } from '@angular/material/datepicker';
import { MatNativeDateModule } from '@angular/material/core';
import { MatIconModule } from '@angular/material/icon';

And in providers (for standalone apps):

importProvidersFrom(
  MatDatepickerModule,
  MatNativeDateModule,
  MatIconModule
)


---

Now the calendar icon will open the calendar correctly! Let me know if you'd like it to look more compact or to appear inline.

